Package edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager

Class TestPlanManager

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.stp.model.manager.TestPlanManager
public class TestPlanManager extends Object
TestPlanManager contains a list of TestPlans, the FailingTestList, and the operations needed to manipulate these lists as well as the test cases and test results contained in them.
Author:
Ryan McPhee, Jeremiah Knizley

  • Constructor Details

    • TestPlanManager

      public TestPlanManager()
      Constructor for the TestPlanManager, constructs testPlans as an empty list. Constructs failingTestList and sets it as the currentTestPlan. isChanged is initialized to false.

  • Method Details

    • loadTestPlans

      public void loadTestPlans(File inputFile)
      Loads TestPlans from a given file. Duplicates are not loaded, invalid plans are not added.
      Parameters:
      inputFile - file to retrieve TestPlans from

    • saveTestPlans

      public void saveTestPlans(File outputFile)
      Saves TestPlans to a given file in the proper format and changes isChanged to false
      Parameters:
      outputFile - file to save TestPlans to

      Returns the state of the isChanged boolean variable

      the isChanged variable of either true or false

    • addTestPlan

      public void addTestPlan(String testPlanName)
      Add a TestPlan to the TestPlanManager's SortedList of TestPlans
      Parameters:
      testPlanName - name of the TestPlan to be added
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if testPlanName is "Failing Tests" or a duplicate of an existing testPlan (case insensitive for both)

    • getTestPlanNames

      public String[] getTestPlanNames()
      Returns a String array of the all the TestPlan names within the TestPlanManager
      Returns:
      String array of TestPlan names

    • setCurrentTestPlan

      public void setCurrentTestPlan(String testPlanName)
      Sets the currentTestPlan to the TestPlan with the given name. If a testPlan with testPlanName is not found, the failingTestList is made current.
      Parameters:
      testPlanName - name of the desired TestPlan to be set as the currentTestPlan

    • getCurrentTestPlan

      public AbstractTestPlan getCurrentTestPlan()
      Returns the currentTestPlan
      Returns:
      the current test plan

    • editTestPlan

      public void editTestPlan(String testPlanName)
      Allows the user to edit the current TestPlan name to the given name
      Parameters:
      testPlanName - desired name to change the current test plan to
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if currentTestPlan is the FailingTestList, or if testPlanName is null, empty, equal to "Failing Tests" (case insensitive), already the name of the TestPlan, or already the name of a TestPlan existing within the testCases list.

    • removeTestPlan

      public void removeTestPlan()
      Removes the current test plan from the manager. Afterwards, the FailingTestList will be the current test plan
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the currentTestPlan is the FailingTestList

    • addTestCase

      public void addTestCase(TestCase t)
      Adds a TestCase to the current test plan
      Parameters:
      t - desired TestCase to be added to the TestPlan

    • addTestResult

      public void addTestResult(int idx, boolean passing, String actualResult)
      Adds TestResult to a TestCase at a given index in the current test plan
      Parameters:
      idx - index of the TestCase desired to be updated with the TestResult
      passing - boolean for whether or not the test is passing
      actualResult - desired actual result to be added to the TestCase
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the given index is outside of the allowed range
      IllegalArgumentException - if the actualResults parameter is null or empty

    • clearTestPlans

      public void clearTestPlans()
      Clears the TestPlans within the TestPlanManager and displays the failing test list
